  "prompt": "Are there international laws against money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several international laws and agreements aimed at preventing money laundering:\n\n1. The Financial Action Task Force (FATF) sets global standards for combating money laundering and terrorist financing.\n\n2. The United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime provides frameworks for international cooperation.\n\n3. The Egmont Group facilitates international information sharing between financial intelligence units.\n\n4. Many countries have signed bilateral and multilateral agreements to combat money laundering.\n\n5. Most developed countries have domestic laws implementing international anti-money laundering (AML) standards.\n\nThese laws typically require financial institutions to:\n- Verify customer identities\n- Report suspicious transactions\n- Maintain transaction records\n- Implement compliance programs\n- Cooperate with law enforcement investigations\n\nPenalties for money laundering can include significant fines and criminal prosecution.",
